title: The Great Race
description: Elly and Pocoyo have a race, and are surprised when an outsider narrowly beats them.

title: Keep Going Pocoyo
description: Pato and Elly are enjoying skipping with a skipping rope. Pocoyo thinks it looks like fun and he wants to skip too. Try as he might though, Pocoyo can't do it. So he asks his friends for help.

title: Twinkle Twinkle
description: Elly finds a beautiful star that has fallen out of the night sky. She loves it and wants to keep it for herself. But Pocoyo makes her realize that the star is for everyone to enjoy. Together they put it back where it's meant to be.

title: The Big Sneeze
description: Elly has a cold and her huge trumpeting sneezes keep knocking Pocoyo's tower of bricks down. Pocoyo and Pato have to work out what to do.

title: Magical Watering Can
description: Pocoyo gives the last drop of water from his watering can to his friends instead of using it to water his musical flowers. Pato and Elly are grateful, so they re-pay the favor.

title: A Dog's Life
description: Pocoyo pretends to be an elephant, a duck and a dog - but when Loula needs his help, Pocoyo sees that sometimes it's best just to be himself.

title: Fetch Loula Fetch!
description: Pocoyo and Loula are going to the beach, but they keep losing their ball. They learn about colors, shapes and sizes as they meet their friends along the way.

title: A Mystery Most Puzzling
description: Pocoyo has to follow the clues in a series of photographs to work out who's got the camera.

title: Let's Go Camping!
description: A camping trip is planned - but Pocoyo and Pato have too much luggage. In the end they realize that all you really need for a nice camping trip are your friends - and then it doesn't really matter whether you're at home or away.

title: Sleepy Bird's Surprise
description: Sleepy Bird's egg takes on a life of its own. Pocoyo and Pato have to get it back to the nest - just in time for it to hatch.

title: Where's Pocoyo?
description: Pocoyo plays hide and seek with us. Can you find him?

title: Bat and Ball
description: It's time for a game of Bat and Ball with Octopus. Everyone wants to have a turn at batting, but the friends learn that you have to wait your turn.

title: A Little Cloud
description: Pocoyo has an unusual new friend: a lonely little cloud who just wants to play.

title: Swept Away
description: Pocoyo shows us that tidying can be fun too: a broom can be a horse, a guitar, or even a hockey stick!

title: A Present for Elly
description: Pocoyo decides to make a very special birthday present for Elly. Can you guess what it is?

title: Hush
description: Pocoyo and his gang want to make friends with a butterfly but every time they say hello, it flies away. With Sleepy Bird's help, they realize how to get close to the butterfly.

title: Drummer Boy
description: Pocoyo wants to drum, but his friends are all busy playing different things. Pocoyo learns that sometimes his friends don't want to do exactly the same things as him.

title: Mystery Footprints
description: Pocoyo and his friends are learning about the different tracks different feet - and paws - make on the ground. When they see some huge footprints they are scared until they realize that one of them is wearing some rather unusual footwear…

title: Having a Ball
description: Pocoyo and Pato are enjoying playing with their new ball. But all of a sudden, the ball takes on a life of its own, and Pocoyo and Pato have to chase it. Who's got the ball…? It's Baby Bird who just wants to play too!

title: Pato's Postal Service
description: When Pocoyo wants to send a letter to Elly, Pato embraces the very important role of postman. After much to-ing and fro-ing, Pato delivers a mammoth package!

title: Fussy Duck
description: Pato, fresh from his shower, is determined to keep clean. Pocoyo and Elly have very different ideas, and Pato soon realizes that half the fun of getting clean is getting dirty in the first place!

title: Puppy Love
description: Pocoyo neglects Loula when he finds a toy dog to play with.

title: Don't Touch!
description: Pocoyo is left in charge of guarding the beautiful castle Elly has built from blocks. Soon Pocoyo can't resist the temptation to touch the castle, and the whole thing comes tumbling down. How can Pocoyo make it up to Elly?

title: Umbrella, Umbrella
description: Pocoyo finds an umbrella. He and his friends have great fun playing with the umbrella and trying to work out what it's for. When it starts to rain, Pocoyo - with the help of the children watching - realizes a perfect use for it!

title: Double Bubble
description: Pocoyo is enjoying blowing bubbles with his bubble maker. Elly wants to play too. They can't agree on who gets to play with it. Finally they realize that the best way to play is to share.

title: Juggling Balls
description: Pocoyo is very impressed with Elly and Octopus' trick of juggling. He wants to play too. Octopus makes Pocoyo practice lots of different activities but Pocoyo can't see the point because they aren't related to juggling… or so he thinks. In the end Pocoyo becomes the star of the show!

title: Hiccup
description: Pato gets the hiccups. Together Pocoyo, Elly and Loula help him to get rid of them by giving him a surprise.

title: Pocoyo, Pocoyo
description: Pocoyo discovers a fabulous new playmate - his echoooo-ooo-ooo-ooo!

title: The Key to it All
description: Pocoyo finds a key which leads him on an exciting and magical adventure of exploration and discovery.

title: Who's on the Phone?
description: Pocoyo finds a phone. He has to work out what it's for, and who's on the other end of the line. It's Elly inviting everyone to a party!

title: Pocoyo Gets it Right
description: Pocoyo wants to play 'pitch and putt' like his friends, Pocoyo and Elly, but he can't quite get the hang of it. He watches carefully and finally grasps where he was going wrong.

title: Pocoyolympics
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Pato stage their own version of the olympics - with a funny and very original variety of contests.

title: Pocoyo Dance
description: Pocoyo finds a radio. Pato does his funny, funky dance and Elly demonstrates her delicate ballet style. Pocoyo hears a tune he likes and finds his groove. Everyone can dance in their own special way!

title: Up Up and Away
description: Our friends are playing with a model airplane which shoots off up into space. They go on an adventure to retrieve the beloved toy, encountering some friendly, bendy aliens along the way.

title: Elly Spots
description: Elly is stricken with a case of the Elly Spots, and Pato and Pocoyo have to forsake their picnic to look after her. Once she is better, she makes it up to them.

title: Drum Roll Please
description: Pocoyo and his playmates love dancing to the Ball Orchestra's music. When it stops, they try to make their own band. Sleepy Bird's snoring sets the rhythm, and together they all make a wonderful, harmonious din.

title: Super Pocoyo
description: Today Pocoyo is Super Pocoyo - a superhero determined to rescue his friends from tight fixes - even when they don't need to be rescued.
